            "@type": "dctypes:Text",
            "format": "text/html",
            "chars": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>LD.I.R13</em></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Tattycoram</strong></p>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-42aa4372-7fff-1f31-7f5b-f81502b8b906\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">We are introduced right away to the nature of Harriet&rsquo;s nickname and to her dissatisfaction; she is a &ldquo;sullen, passionate girl&rdquo; (LD 25). Mr. Meagles explains: &ldquo;Why, she was called in the Institution, Harriet Beadle&ndash;an arbitrary name, of course. Now, Harriet we changed into Hatty, and then into Tatty, because, as practical people, we thought even a playful name might be a new thing to her, and might have a softening and affectionate kind of effect&rdquo; (18).</p>"
